</svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mwa1665702882785.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mwa1665702882785.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mwa1665702882785.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mwa1665702882785\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">prf \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the TCP/IP version preference to TCP4 (IPv4) or TCP6 (IPv6).\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"mwa1665702882785__topic_d32300e1_d32301e1_d32302e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mwa1665702882785__p_d32303e1_d32304e1_d32305e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TCP_PARAMS</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">prf</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">4</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">6</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mwa1665702882785__section_jsk_fph_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059945e76\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mwa1665702882785__p_d32309e1_d32310e1_d32311e1\">This option can be set in all assignment files.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mwa1665702882785__section_vkh_gph_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059945e85\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mwa1665702882785__p_d32315e1_d32316e1_d32317e1\">When there is a choice in your TCP environment, use\n            this parameter to specify your preference for the TCP protocol version. If there is no\n            choice, for example, if your TCP supports only TCP4 or only TCP6, then your specified\n            preference is ignored. If not present, TCP4 is the default.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vsu1665702524699.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Host Identification for TCP/IP and TLS</a><p>The TCP and TLS connectors support both the TCP4 (IPv4) and TCP6 (IPv6) protocols. The protocol used depends on the format of the IP address of the host, and how it is specified.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530112\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530112\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "prf Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 prf Set the TCP/IP version preference to TCP4 (IPv4) or TCP6 (IPv6). USYS$TCP_PARAMS { = } prf = 4 | 6 Use This option can be set in all assignment files. Description When there is a choice in your TCP environment, use this parameter to specify your preference for the TCP protocol version. If there is no choice, for example, if your TCP supports only TCP4 or only TCP6, then your specified preference is ignored. If not present, TCP4 is the default. Related Links Host Identification for TCP/IP and TLS The TCP and TLS connectors support both the TCP4 (IPv4) and TCP6 (IPv6) protocols. The protocol used depends on the format of the IP address of the host, and how it is specified. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}